# Experimental Results and Architecture Validation

The development of 5DMarkets V2 has focused on testing the central hypothesis that financial markets can be modeled as a deformable high-dimensional dynamical system analogous to 5D Computed Tomography (5DCT) motion modeling.

The primary objective of early experiments has been to determine whether the architecture can learn synthetic market dynamics when those dynamics are explicitly governed by structured interacting force systems.

The experiments below document the iterative development process and the empirical findings that have shaped the current architecture.

---

