Experiment 3 — Information Bottleneck Diagnosis
Objective

Test whether global averaging was destroying predictive information.

Hypothesis

The architecture originally collapsed all asset-level information into a single global state vector.

Original operation:

fused = torch.mean(fused, dim=1)

This transformed:

[50,64]→[64]

The hypothesis was:

Global averaging destroys local asset deformation information necessary for prediction.

Equivalent theoretical statement:

