where:

M = local market field
M̄ = globally averaged market state
Architecture Modification

Global averaging removed.

Instead:

fused = fused.view(batch,-1)

which preserved all asset-level structure.

New dimensionality:

[50,64]→[3200]

The full market state was passed directly into temporal memory.

Results

Early training showed dramatically improved convergence.

Epoch 0 Loss: 1.0049

Epoch 11 Loss: 0.7684

However, the training process eventually crashed due to computational limitations.

The 3200-dimensional recurrent memory layer exceeded available compute resources.

Interpretation

This experiment strongly supported the hypothesis.

Preserving local asset structure dramatically improved learning.

However, direct recurrent modeling of the full market state proved computationally inefficient.

